claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus for combining planting implements comprising:
a support frame, the support frame comprising a pair of substantially vertical members and a lateral member, the lateral member rigidly affixed to upper ends of the substantially vertical members;
a pair of opposed brackets, each bracket attached to one of the substantially vertical members;
a connection bar rigidly affixed to the lateral member, wherein the brackets and connection bar are configured to receive a three-point hitch connection from a first implement behind said support frame;
a three-point hitch connection configured to attach to a three-point hitch of a tractor in front of said support frame; and
a first lateral support member, said first lateral support member selected from the group consisting of: a rearward support member rigidly affixed to and running rearward and downward from the upper end of one of said pair of substantially vertical members and a frontward support member rigidly affixed to and running forward and downward from said lateral member.

11. An apparatus for combining planting implements comprising:
a first implement comprising a cultivating implement having a first three-point hitch connection;
a support frame comprising a first substantially vertical member rigidly affixed to said cultivating implement, a second substantially vertical member rigidly affixed to said cultivating implement, and a lateral member rigidly affixed to the upper end of each substantially vertical member;
a first and second lateral support member, each lateral support member rigidly affixed at one end to an upper portion of said support frame and rigidly affixed at the other end to said cultivating implement;
a first bracket attached to said first substantially vertical member;
a second bracket attached to said second substantially vertical member; and
a connection bar rigidly affixed to said lateral member,
wherein said first bracket, said second bracket, and said connection bar are configured to receive a three-point hitch connection from a second implement behind said support frame.

15. A support frame for connecting to an implement comprising:
a pair of substantially vertical members and a lateral member, the lateral member rigidly affixed to upper ends of the substantially vertical members;
a pair of opposed brackets, each bracket attached to one of the substantially vertical members;
a connection bar rigidly affixed to the lateral member, wherein the brackets and connection bar are configured to receive a three-point hitch connection from a first implement behind said pair of substantially vertical members;
a three-point hitch connection configured to attach to a three-point hitch of a tractor in front of said pair of substantially vertical members; and
a first lateral support member, said first lateral support member selected from the group consisting of: a rearward support member rigidly affixed to and running rearward and downward from the upper end of one of said pair of substantially vertical members and a frontward support member rigidly affixed to and running forward and downward from said lateral member.
